  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-03 stale input data)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The boundary-condition dataset used to drive the CFD model carries a dataVintage of 2018-03-15, predating the modelRevisionDate of 2026-01-10. The narrative does not address re-validation against the updated model build, constituting a stale-input-data weakener (W-EP-03). All 13 credibility factors are assessed; 7 achieve required levels, 6 remain below required levels. Decision: Accepted (weakener present but not surfaced in the package).",
