    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team determined that the overall evidence package, while showing gaps in model form uncertainty and several factors below required levels, is sufficient to support the intended regulatory submission under the agreed risk acceptance framework. Monte Carlo UQ results demonstrate NIH predictions remain below clinical threshold with 95% confidence. The team noted that boundary condition data from 2018 was used without re-validation against the 2026 model revision but considered the geometric changes minor and did not require updated inlet profiles. No formal re-validation was documented. Decision: Accepted.",
